  <Subject Subject_ID="300211253">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300211289</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>water sports equipment [300211289], sports and athletic equipment [300211035], recreational artifacts (equipment) [300218781], Recreational Artifacts (hierarchy name) [300136012], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long, wide buoyant boards, anywhere from 4 to 12 feet long and about 3 feet wide at the maximum point and usually having slight curves, especially in the front, used for riding surf. Originally constructed of wood, since the 1960s they have most often been made from synthetic foam covered in resin-coated fiberglass.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tablas flotadoras largas y anchas, generalmente de 5 a 6 pies de largo y cerca de 3 pies de ancho en el punto máximo y que usualmente tienen leves curvas, especialmente en la parte delantera, usadas para deslizarse sobre las olas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lange, brede, drijvende planken van meestal zo'n 1,50 tot 1,80 m lang en 0,90 m breed op het breedste gedeelte en meestal met lichte rondingen, vooral aan de voorkant, om op de branding mee te surfen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>長且寬的浮板，長度在4至12呎之間，最寬可達三呎，通常前方會微彎，作衝浪之用。起初多為木製，但自1960年代起，多以樹脂玻璃纖維包覆合成泡沫塑料製成。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Langes, breites, schwimmenfähiges Brett, zwischen 1,2 bis 3,5 m lang und maximal etwa 0,9 m breit, in der Regel vor allem an der Front gerundet und für das Wellenreiten genutzt. Ursprünglich aus Holz gefertigt wurde es seit den 1960er Jahren in den meisten Fällen aus synthetischem Schaumstoff hergestellt, der mit harzbeschichtetem Fiberglas bedeckt ist.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
